‚úÖ 1. Daily Backup Script

üìÇ Requirement
Take backup of /home
Store in /backup
Keep date-wise backups



vim daily_backup.sh
#!/bin/bash

SRC="/home"
DEST="/backup"
DATE=$(date +%F)

mkdir -p $DEST
tar -czf $DEST/home_backup_$DATE.tar.gz $SRC

echo "Backup completed on $DATE" >> /var/log/backup.log



‚è∞ Cron Job
0 2 * * * /bin/bash /root/scripts/daily_backup.sh

************************************************************************************


‚úÖ 2. Log Cleanup Script

üìÇ Requirement
Delete .log files older than 7 days
Path: /var/log


vim log_cleanup.sh

#!/bin/bash

LOG_PATH="/var/log"
find $LOG_PATH -type f -name "*.log" -mtime +7 -exec rm -f {} \;

echo "Old logs cleaned on $(date)" >> /var/log/log_cleanup.log

‚è∞ Cron Job
0 3 * * * /bin/bash /root/scripts/log_cleanup.sh

************************************************************************************
‚úÖ 3. User Creation Script (Automation)
üìÇ Requirement
Create user with password
Ask username from admin


vm user_create.sh
#!/bin/bash

read -p "Enter username: " USER
read -s -p "Enter password: " PASS
echo

useradd $USER
echo "$USER:$PASS" | chpasswd

echo "User $USER created successfully"
***************
‚ñ∂ Run
bash user_create.sh

************************************************************************************


‚úÖ 4. Disk Usage Alert Script (with Mail)

üìÇ Requirement
Alert if disk usage > 80%
Send mail to admin

vim disk_alert.sh

#!/bin/bash

THRESHOLD=80
EMAIL="admin@example.com"

USAGE=$(df / | awk 'NR==2 {print $5}' | sed 's/%//')

if [ $USAGE -gt $THRESHOLD ]; then
    echo "Disk usage is $USAGE%" | mail -s "Disk Alert on Server" $EMAIL
fi


‚è∞ Cron Job
*/30 * * * * /bin/bash /root/scripts/disk_alert.sh

************************************************************************************
‚úÖ 5. CPU & Memory Monitoring Script

üìÇ Requirement
Check CPU & RAM
Send alert if high usage


vim cpu_mem_monitor.sh

#!/bin/bash

CPU=$(top -bn1 | grep "Cpu(s)" | awk '{print $2 + $4}')
MEM=$(free | awk '/Mem/ {printf("%.0f"), $3/$2 * 100}')
EMAIL="admin@example.com"

if [ $CPU -gt 80 ] || [ $MEM -gt 80 ]; then
    echo "High Usage Alert
CPU: $CPU%
Memory: $MEM%" | mail -s "CPU/Memory Alert" $EMAIL
fi



‚è∞ Cron Job
*/10 * * * * /bin/bash /root/scripts/cpu_mem_monitor.sh
************************************************************************************





























